  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the oven to 375\u00061\u00020F (190\u00061\u00020C).",
    "Roll out the all-purpose flour and butter mixture to a thickness of about 1/8 inch.",
    "Transfer the dough to a 9-inch tart pan with a removable bottom.",
    "Bake the crust for 18 minutes or until lightly golden.",
    "In a separate bowl, whisk together the shio-koji-cure, black pepper, allspice, eggs, heavy cream, grated cheddar cheese, minced fresh chives, kosher salt, white pepper, and cold water.",
    "Pour the filling into the baked tart crust and smooth the top.",
    "Return the tart to the oven and bake for an additional 25 minutes or until the filling is set.",
    "Allow the tart to cool to room temperature before serving.",
    "Cover the tart with plastic wrap and refrigerate for at least 30 minutes before serving.",
    "If the tart does not set properly, refrigerate for an additional 30 minutes or until it has reached the desired consistency."
